editor.label: Body:
editor.tooltip: Specifies a string that is the comment.

editor.label: Annotated Element:
editor.tooltip: References the Element(s) being commented.

editor.label: Owned Element:
editor.tooltip: The Elements owned by this element.

editor.label: Owner:
editor.tooltip: The Element that owns this element.

editor.label: Owned Comment:
editor.tooltip: The Comments owned by this element.

editor.label: Owned Type:
editor.tooltip: References the packaged elements that are Types.

editor.label: Package Merge:
editor.tooltip: References the PackageMerges that are owned by this Package.

editor.label: Packaged Element:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the packageable elements that are owned by this Package.

editor.label: Nested Package:
editor.tooltip: References the packaged elements that are Packages.

editor.label: Nesting Package:
editor.tooltip: References the Package that owns this Package.

editor.label: Profile Application:
editor.tooltip: References the ProfileApplications that indicate which profiles have been applied to the Package.

editor.label: Name:
editor.tooltip: The name of the NamedElement.

editor.label: Visibility:
editor.tooltip: Determines where the NamedElement appears within different Namespaces within the overall model, and its accessibility.

editor.label: Client Dependency:
editor.tooltip: Indicates the dependencies that reference the client.

editor.label: Namespace:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the namespace that owns the NamedElement.

editor.label: Name Expression:
editor.tooltip: The string expression used to define the name of this named element.

editor.label: Supplier:
editor.tooltip: The element(s) independent of the client element(s), in the same respect and the same dependency relationship. In some directed dependency relationships (such as Refinement Abstractions), a common convention in the domain of class-based OO software is to put the more abstract element in this role. Despite this convention, users of UML may stipulate a sense of dependency suitable for their domain, which makes a more abstract element dependent on that which is more specific.

editor.label: Client:
editor.tooltip: The element(s) dependent on the supplier element(s). In some cases (such as a Trace Abstraction) the assignment of direction (that is, the designation of the client element) is at the discretion of the modeler, and is a stipulation.

editor.label: Source:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the sources of the DirectedRelationship.

editor.label: Target:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the targets of the DirectedRelationship.

editor.label: Related Element:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the elements related by the Relationship.

editor.label: Element Import:
editor.tooltip: References the ElementImports owned by the Namespace.

editor.label: Package Import:
editor.tooltip: References the PackageImports owned by the Namespace.

editor.label: Owned Rule:
editor.tooltip: Specifies a set of Constraints owned by this Namespace.

editor.label: Member:
editor.tooltip: A collection of NamedElements identifiable within the Namespace, either by being owned or by being introduced by importing or inheritance.

editor.label: Imported Member:
editor.tooltip: References the PackageableElements that are members of this Namespace as a result of either PackageImports or ElementImports.

editor.label: Owned Member:
editor.tooltip: A collection of NamedElements owned by the Namespace.

editor.label: Visibility:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the visibility of the imported PackageableElement within the importing Package. The default visibility is the same as that of the imported element. If the imported element does not have a visibility, it is possible to add visibility to the element import.

editor.label: Alias:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the name that should be added to the namespace of the importing package in lieu of the name of the imported packagable element. The aliased name must not clash with any other member name in the importing package. By default, no alias is used.

editor.label: Imported Element:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the PackageableElement whose name is to be added to a Namespace.

editor.label: Importing Namespace:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the Namespace that imports a PackageableElement from another Package.

editor.label: Visibility:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the visibility of the imported PackageableElements within the importing Namespace, i.e., whether imported elements will in turn be visible to other packages that use that importingPackage as an importedPackage. If the PackageImport is public, the imported elements will be visible outside the package, while if it is private they will not.

editor.label: Imported Package:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the Package whose members are imported into a Namespace.

editor.label: Importing Namespace:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the Namespace that imports the members from a Package.

editor.label: Constrained Element:
editor.tooltip: The ordered set of Elements referenced by this Constraint.

editor.label: Specification:
editor.tooltip: A condition that must be true when evaluated in order for the constraint to be satisfied.

editor.label: Context:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the namespace that owns the NamedElement.

editor.label: Type:
editor.tooltip: This information is derived from the return result for this Operation.The type of the TypedElement.

editor.label: Package:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the owning package of this classifier, if any.

editor.label: Is Derived:
editor.tooltip: Specifies whether the association is derived from other model elements such as other associations or constraints.

editor.label: Owned End:
editor.tooltip: The ends that are owned by the association itself.

editor.label: Member End:
editor.tooltip: Each end represents participation of instances of the classifier connected to the end in links of the association.

editor.label: End Type:
editor.tooltip: References the classifiers that are used as types of the ends of the association.

editor.label: Navigable Owned End:
editor.tooltip: The navigable ends that are owned by the association itself.

editor.label: Is Abstract:
editor.tooltip: If true, the Classifier does not provide a complete declaration and can typically not be instantiated. An abstract classifier is intended to be used by other classifiers e.g. as the target of general metarelationships or generalization relationships.

editor.label: Generalization:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the Generalization relationships for this Classifier. These Generalizations navigaten to more general classifiers in the generalization hierarchy.

editor.label: Powertype Extent:
editor.tooltip: Designates the GeneralizationSet of which the associated Classifier is a power type.

editor.label: Feature:
editor.tooltip: Note that there may be members of the Classifier that are of the type Feature but are not included in this association, e.g. inherited features.Specifies each feature defined in the classifier.

editor.label: Inherited Member:
editor.tooltip: Specifies all elements inherited by this classifier from the general classifiers.

editor.label: Redefined Classifier:
editor.tooltip: References the Classifiers that are redefined by this Classifier.

editor.label: General:
editor.tooltip: References the general classifier in the Generalization relationship.Specifies the general Classifiers for this Classifier.

editor.label: Substitution:
editor.tooltip: References the substitutions that are owned by this Classifier.

editor.label: Attribute:
editor.tooltip: Refers to all of the Properties that are direct (i.e. not inherited or imported) attributes of the classifier.

editor.label: Representation:
editor.tooltip: References a collaboration use which indicates the collaboration that represents this classifier.

editor.label: Collaboration Use:
editor.tooltip: References the collaboration uses owned by the classifier.

editor.label: Owned Use Case:
editor.tooltip: References the use cases owned by this classifier.

editor.label: Use Case:
editor.tooltip: The set of use cases for which this Classifier is the subject.

editor.label: Is Leaf:
editor.tooltip: Indicates whether it is possible to further specialize a RedefinableElement. If the value is true, then it is not possible to further specialize the RedefinableElement.

editor.label: Redefined Element:
editor.tooltip: The redefinable element that is being redefined by this element.

editor.label: Redefinition Context:
editor.tooltip: References the contexts that this element may be redefined from.

editor.label: Template Binding:
editor.tooltip: The optional bindings from this element to templates.

editor.label: Owned Template Signature:
editor.tooltip: The optional template signature specifying the formal template parameters.

editor.label: Signature:
editor.tooltip: The template signature for the template that is the target of the binding.

editor.label: Parameter Substitution:
editor.tooltip: The parameter substitutions owned by this template binding.

editor.label: Bound Element:
editor.tooltip: The element that is bound by this binding.

editor.label: Parameter:
editor.tooltip: The ordered set of all formal template parameters for this template signature.

editor.label: Owned Parameter:
editor.tooltip: The formal template parameters that are owned by this template signature.

editor.label: Template:
editor.tooltip: The element that owns this template signature.

editor.label: Signature:
editor.tooltip: The template signature that owns this template parameter.

editor.label: Parametered Element:
editor.tooltip: The element exposed by this template parameter.

editor.label: Owned Parametered Element:
editor.tooltip: The element that is owned by this template parameter.

editor.label: Default:
editor.tooltip: The element that is the default for this formal template parameter.

editor.label: Owned Default:
editor.tooltip: The element that is owned by this template parameter for the purpose of providing a default.

editor.label: Owning Template Parameter:
editor.tooltip: The formal template parameter that owns this element.

editor.label: Template Parameter:
editor.tooltip: The template parameter that exposes this element as a formal parameter.

editor.label: Formal:
editor.tooltip: The formal template parameter that is associated with this substitution.

editor.label: Actual:
editor.tooltip: The element that is the actual parameter for this substitution.

editor.label: Owned Actual:
editor.tooltip: The actual parameter that is owned by this substitution.

editor.label: Template Binding:
editor.tooltip: The optional bindings from this element to templates.

editor.label: Is Substitutable:
editor.tooltip: Indicates whether the specific classifier can be used wherever the general classifier can be used. If true, the execution traces of the specific classifier will be a superset of the execution traces of the general classifier.

editor.label: General:
editor.tooltip: References the general classifier in the Generalization relationship.

editor.label: Generalization Set:
editor.tooltip: Designates a set in which instances of Generalization is considered members.

editor.label: Specific:
editor.tooltip: References the specializing classifier in the Generalization relationship.

editor.label: Is Covering:
editor.tooltip: Indicates (via the associated Generalizations) whether or not the set of specific Classifiers are covering for a particular general classifier. When isCovering is true, every instance of a particular general Classifier is also an instance of at least one of its specific Classifiers for the GeneralizationSet. When isCovering is false, there are one or more instances of the particular general Classifier that are not instances of at least one of its specific Classifiers defined for the GeneralizationSet.

editor.label: Is Disjoint:
editor.tooltip: Indicates whether or not the set of specific Classifiers in a Generalization relationship have instance in common. If isDisjoint is true, the specific Classifiers for a particular GeneralizationSet have no members in common; that is, their intersection is empty. If isDisjoint is false, the specific Classifiers in a particular GeneralizationSet have one or more members in common; that is, their intersection is not empty. For example, Person could have two Generalization relationships, each with the different specific Classifier: Manager or Staff. This would be disjoint because every instance of Person must either be a Manager or Staff. In contrast, Person could have two Generalization relationships involving two specific (and non-covering) Classifiers: Sales Person and Manager. This GeneralizationSet would not be disjoint because there are instances of Person which can be a Sales Person and a Manager.

editor.label: Powertype:
editor.tooltip: Designates the Classifier that is defined as the power type for the associated GeneralizationSet.

editor.label: Generalization:
editor.tooltip: Designates the instances of Generalization which are members of a given GeneralizationSet.

editor.label: Is Static:
editor.tooltip: Specifies whether this feature characterizes individual instances classified by the classifier (false) or the classifier itself (true).

editor.label: Featuring Classifier:
editor.tooltip: The Classifiers that have this Feature as a feature.

editor.label: Contract:
editor.tooltip: The contract with which the substituting classifier complies.

editor.label: Substituting Classifier:
editor.tooltip: Instances of the substituting classifier are runtime substitutable where instances of the contract classifier are expected.

editor.label: Mapping:
editor.tooltip: An composition of an Expression that states the abstraction relationship between the supplier and the client. In some cases, such as Derivation, it is usually formal and unidirectional; in other cases, such as Trace, it is usually informal and bidirectional. The mapping expression is optional and may be omitted if the precise relationship between the elements is not specified.

editor.label: Body:
editor.tooltip: The text of the expression, possibly in multiple languages.

editor.label: Language:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the languages in which the expression is stated. The interpretation of the expression body depends on the languages. If the languages are unspecified, they might be implicit from the expression body or the context. Languages are matched to body strings by order.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: Restricts an opaque expression to return exactly one return result. When the invocation of the opaque expression completes, a single set of values is returned to its owner. This association is derived from the single return result parameter of the associated behavior.

editor.label: Behavior:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the behavior of the opaque expression.

editor.label: Direction:
editor.tooltip: Indicates whether a parameter is being sent into or out of a behavioral element.

editor.label: Is Exception:
editor.tooltip: Tells whether an output parameter may emit a value to the exclusion of the other outputs.

editor.label: Is Stream:
editor.tooltip: Tells whether an input parameter may accept values while its behavior is executing, or whether an output parameter post values while the behavior is executing.

editor.label: Effect:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the effect that the owner of the parameter has on values passed in or out of the parameter.

editor.label: Parameter Set:
editor.tooltip: The parameter sets containing the parameter. See ParameterSet.

editor.label: Operation:
editor.tooltip: References the Operation owning this parameter.

editor.label: Default Value:
editor.tooltip: Specifies a ValueSpecification that represents a value to be used when no argument is supplied for the Parameter.

editor.label: Is Ordered:
editor.tooltip: For a multivalued multiplicity, this attribute specifies whether the values in an instantiation of this element are sequentially ordered.

editor.label: Is Unique:
editor.tooltip: For a multivalued multiplicity, this attributes specifies whether the values in an instantiation of this element are unique.

editor.label: Upper Value:
editor.tooltip: The specification of the upper bound for this multiplicity.

editor.label: Lower Value:
editor.tooltip: The specification of the lower bound for this multiplicity.

editor.label: End:
editor.tooltip: Denotes a connector that attaches to this connectable element.

editor.label: Defining End:
editor.tooltip: A derived association referencing the corresponding association end on the association which types the connector owing this connector end. This association is derived by selecting the association end at the same place in the ordering of association ends as this connector end.

editor.label: Role:
editor.tooltip: The connectable element attached at this connector end. When an instance of the containing classifier is created, a link may (depending on the multiplicities) be created to an instance of the classifier that types this connectable element.

editor.label: Part With Port:
editor.tooltip: Indicates the role of the internal structure of a classifier with the port to which the connector end is attached.

editor.label: Is Derived:
editor.tooltip: If isDerived is true, the value of the attribute is derived from information elsewhere.Specifies whether the Property is derived, i.e., whether its value or values can be computed from other information.

editor.label: Is Derived Union:
editor.tooltip: Specifies whether the property is derived as the union of all of the properties that are constrained to subset it.

editor.label: Aggregation:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the kind of aggregation that applies to the Property.

editor.label: Class:
editor.tooltip: References the Class that owns the Property.

editor.label: Datatype:
editor.tooltip: The DataType that owns this Property.

editor.label: Redefined Property:
editor.tooltip: References the properties that are redefined by this property.

editor.label: Owning Association:
editor.tooltip: References the owning association of this property, if any.

editor.label: Default Value:
editor.tooltip: A ValueSpecification that is evaluated to give a default value for the Property when an object of the owning Classifier is instantiated.

editor.label: Opposite:
editor.tooltip: In the case where the property is one navigable end of a binary association with both ends navigable, this gives the other end.

editor.label: Subsetted Property:
editor.tooltip: References the properties of which this property is constrained to be a subset.

editor.label: Association:
editor.tooltip: References the association of which this property is a member, if any.

editor.label: Qualifier:
editor.tooltip: An optional list of ordered qualifier attributes for the end. If the list is empty, then the Association is not qualified.

editor.label: Association End:
editor.tooltip: Designates the optional association end that owns a qualifier attribute.

editor.label: Deployment:
editor.tooltip: The set of Deployments for a DeploymentTarget.

editor.label: Deployed Element:
editor.tooltip: The set of elements that are manifested in an Artifact that is involved in Deployment to a DeploymentTarget.

editor.label: Deployed Artifact:
editor.tooltip: The Artifacts that are deployed onto a Node. This association specializes the supplier association.

editor.label: Configuration:
editor.tooltip: The specification of properties that parameterize the deployment and execution of one or more Artifacts.

editor.label: Location:
editor.tooltip: The DeployedTarget which is the target of a Deployment.

editor.label: Deployment Location:
editor.tooltip: The location where an Artifact is deployed onto a Node. This is typically a 'directory' or 'memory address'.

editor.label: Execution Location:
editor.tooltip: The location where a component Artifact executes. This may be a local or remote location.

editor.label: Deployment:
editor.tooltip: The deployment with which the DeploymentSpecification is associated.

editor.label: File Name:
editor.tooltip: A concrete name that is used to refer to the Artifact in a physical context. Example: file system name, universal resource locator.

editor.label: Nested Artifact:
editor.tooltip: The Artifacts that are defined (nested) within the Artifact.The association is a specialization of the ownedMember association from Namespace to NamedElement.

editor.label: Manifestation:
editor.tooltip: The set of model elements that are manifested in the Artifact. That is, these model elements are utilized in the construction (or generation) of the artifact.

editor.label: Owned Operation:
editor.tooltip: The Operations defined for the Artifact. The association is a specialization of the ownedMember association.

editor.label: Owned Attribute:
editor.tooltip: The attributes or association ends defined for the Artifact.The association is a specialization of the ownedMember association.

editor.label: Utilized Element:
editor.tooltip: The model element that is utilized in the manifestation in an Artifact.

editor.label: Is Query:
editor.tooltip: Specifies whether an execution of the BehavioralFeature leaves the state of the system unchanged (isQuery=true) or whether side effects may occur (isQuery=false).

editor.label: Interface:
editor.tooltip: The Interface that owns this Operation.

editor.label: Class:
editor.tooltip: The class that owns the operation.

editor.label: Precondition:
editor.tooltip: An optional set of Constraints on the state of the system when the Operation is invoked.

editor.label: Postcondition:
editor.tooltip: An optional set of Constraints specifying the state of the system when the Operation is completed.

editor.label: Redefined Operation:
editor.tooltip: References the Operations that are redefined by this Operation.

editor.label: Datatype:
editor.tooltip: The DataType that owns this Operation.

editor.label: Body Condition:
editor.tooltip: An optional Constraint on the result values of an invocation of this Operation.

editor.label: Type:
editor.tooltip: This information is derived from the return result for this Operation.Specifies the return result of the operation, if present.

editor.label: Is Abstract:
editor.tooltip: If true, then the behavioral feature does not have an implementation, and one must be supplied by a more specific element. If false, the behavioral feature must have an implementation in the classifier or one must be inherited from a more general element.

editor.label: Concurrency:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the semantics of concurrent calls to the same passive instance (i.e., an instance originating from a class with isActive being false). Active instances control access to their own behavioral features.

editor.label: Owned Parameter:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the ordered set of formal parameters of this BehavioralFeature.

editor.label: Method:
editor.tooltip: A behavioral description that implements the behavioral feature. There may be at most one behavior for a particular pairing of a classifier (as owner of the behavior) and a behavioral feature (as specification of the behavior).

editor.label: Raised Exception:
editor.tooltip: References the Types representing exceptions that may be raised during an invocation of this feature.The signals that the behavioral feature raises as exceptions.

editor.label: Owned Parameter Set:
editor.tooltip: The ParameterSets owned by this BehavioralFeature.

editor.label: Is Reentrant:
editor.tooltip: Tells whether the behavior can be invoked while it is still executing from a previous invocation.

editor.label: Redefined Behavior:
editor.tooltip: References a behavior that this behavior redefines. A subtype of Behavior may redefine any other subtype of Behavior. If the behavior implements a behavioral feature, it replaces the redefined behavior. If the behavior is a classifier behavior, it extends the redefined behavior.

editor.label: Owned Parameter:
editor.tooltip: References a list of parameters to the behavior which describes the order and type of arguments that can be given when the behavior is invoked and of the values which will be returned when the behavior completes its execution.

editor.label: Context:
editor.tooltip: The classifier that is the context for the execution of the behavior. If the behavior is owned by a BehavioredClassifier, that classifier is the context. Otherwise, the context is the first BehavioredClassifier reached by following the chain of owner relationships. For example, following this algorithm, the context of an entry action in a state machine is the classifier that owns the state machine. The features of the context classifier as well as the elements visible to the context classifier are visible to the behavior.

editor.label: Precondition:
editor.tooltip: An optional set of Constraints specifying what must be fulfilled when the behavior is invoked.

editor.label: Postcondition:
editor.tooltip: An optional set of Constraints specifying what is fulfilled after the execution of the behavior is completed, if its precondition was fulfilled before its invocation.

editor.label: Owned Parameter Set:
editor.tooltip: The ParameterSets owned by this Behavior.

editor.label: Specification:
editor.tooltip: Designates a behavioral feature that the behavior implements. The behavioral feature must be owned by the classifier that owns the behavior or be inherited by it. The parameters of the behavioral feature and the implementing behavior must match. A behavior does not need to have a specification, in which case it either is the classifer behavior of a BehavioredClassifier or it can only be invoked by another behavior of the classifier.

editor.label: Is Active:
editor.tooltip: Determines whether an object specified by this class is active or not. If true, then the owning class is referred to as an active class. If false, then such a class is referred to as a passive class.

editor.label: Nested Classifier:
editor.tooltip: References all the Classifiers that are defined (nested) within the Class.

editor.label: Owned Operation:
editor.tooltip: The operations owned by the class.

editor.label: Super Class:
editor.tooltip: This gives the superclasses of a class.

editor.label: Owned Reception:
editor.tooltip: Receptions that objects of this class are willing to accept.

editor.label: Extension:
editor.tooltip: References the Extensions that specify additional properties of the metaclass. The property is derived from the extensions whose memberEnds are typed by the Class.

editor.label: Owned Behavior:
editor.tooltip: References behavior specifications owned by a classifier.

editor.label: Classifier Behavior:
editor.tooltip: A behavior specification that specifies the behavior of the classifier itself.

editor.label: Interface Realization:
editor.tooltip: The set of InterfaceRealizations owned by the BehavioredClassifier. Interface realizations reference the Interfaces of which the BehavioredClassifier is an implementation.

editor.label: Owned Trigger:
editor.tooltip: References Trigger descriptions owned by a Classifier.

editor.label: Contract:
editor.tooltip: References the Interface specifying the conformance contract.

editor.label: Implementing Classifier:
editor.tooltip: References the BehavioredClassifier that owns this Interfacerealization (i.e., the classifier that realizes the Interface to which it points).

editor.label: Owned Attribute:
editor.tooltip: The attributes (i.e. the properties) owned by the class.

editor.label: Owned Operation:
editor.tooltip: The operations owned by the class.

editor.label: Nested Classifier:
editor.tooltip: References all the Classifiers that are defined (nested) within the Class.

editor.label: Redefined Interface:
editor.tooltip: References all the Interfaces redefined by this Interface.

editor.label: Owned Reception:
editor.tooltip: Receptions that objects providing this interface are willing to accept.

editor.label: Protocol:
editor.tooltip: References a protocol state machine specifying the legal sequences of the invocation of the behavioral features described in the interface.

editor.label: Signal:
editor.tooltip: The signal that this reception handles.

editor.label: Owned Attribute:
editor.tooltip: The attributes owned by the signal.

editor.label: Conformance:
editor.tooltip: Conformance between protocol state machines.

editor.label: Region:
editor.tooltip: The regions owned directly by the state machine.

editor.label: Submachine State:
editor.tooltip: References the submachine(s) in case of a submachine state. Multiple machines are referenced in case of a concurrent state.

editor.label: Connection Point:
editor.tooltip: The connection points defined for this state machine. They represent the interface of the state machine when used as part of submachine state.

editor.label: Extended State Machine:
editor.tooltip: The state machines of which this is an extension.

editor.label: Subvertex:
editor.tooltip: The set of vertices that are owned by this region.

editor.label: Transition:
editor.tooltip: The set of transitions owned by the region. Note that internal transitions are owned by a region, but applies to the source state.

editor.label: State:
editor.tooltip: The State that owns the Region. If a Region is owned by a State, then it cannot also be owned by a StateMachine.

editor.label: Extended Region:
editor.tooltip: The region of which this region is an extension.

editor.label: State Machine:
editor.tooltip: The StateMachine that owns the Region. If a Region is owned by a StateMachine, then it cannot also be owned by a State.

editor.label: Outgoing:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the transitions departing from this vertex.

editor.label: Incoming:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the transitions entering this vertex.

editor.label: Container:
editor.tooltip: The region that contains this vertex.

editor.label: Kind:
editor.tooltip: Indicates the precise type of the transition.

editor.label: Container:
editor.tooltip: Designates the region that owns this transition.

editor.label: Source:
editor.tooltip: Designates the originating vertex (state or pseudostate) of the transition.

editor.label: Target:
editor.tooltip: Designates the target vertex that is reached when the transition is taken.

editor.label: Redefined Transition:
editor.tooltip: The transition that is redefined by this transition.

editor.label: Guard:
editor.tooltip: A guard is a constraint that provides a fine-grained control over the firing of the transition. The guard is evaluated when an event occurrence is dispatched by the state machine. If the guard is true at that time, the transition may be enabled, otherwise, it is disabled. Guards should be pure expressions without side effects. Guard expressions with side effects are ill formed.

editor.label: Effect:
editor.tooltip: Specifies an optional behavior to be performed when the transition fires.

editor.label: Trigger:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the triggers that may fire the transition.

editor.label: Event:
editor.tooltip: The event that causes the trigger.

editor.label: Port:
editor.tooltip: A optional port of the receiver object on which the behavioral feature is invoked.

editor.label: Is Behavior:
editor.tooltip: Specifies whether requests arriving at this port are sent to the classifier behavior of this classifier. Such ports are referred to as behavior port. Any invocation of a behavioral feature targeted at a behavior port will be handled by the instance of the owning classifier itself, rather than by any instances that this classifier may contain.

editor.label: Is Service:
editor.tooltip: If true indicates that this port is used to provide the published functionality of a classifier; if false, this port is used to implement the classifier but is not part of the essential externally-visible functionality of the classifier and can, therefore, be altered or deleted along with the internal implementation of the classifier and other properties that are considered part of its implementation.

editor.label: Required:
editor.tooltip: References the interfaces specifying the set of operations and receptions which the classifier expects its environment to handle. This association is derived as the set of interfaces required by the type of the port or its supertypes.

editor.label: Redefined Port:
editor.tooltip: A port may be redefined when its containing classifier is specialized. The redefining port may have additional interfaces to those that are associated with the redefined port or it may replace an interface by one of its subtypes.

editor.label: Provided:
editor.tooltip: References the interfaces specifying the set of operations and receptions which the classifier offers to its environment, and which it will handle either directly or by forwarding it to a part of its internal structure. This association is derived from the interfaces realized by the type of the port or by the type of the port, if the port was typed by an interface.

editor.label: Protocol:
editor.tooltip: References an optional protocol state machine which describes valid interactions at this interaction point.

editor.label: Submachine:
editor.tooltip: The state machine that is to be inserted in place of the (submachine) state.

editor.label: Connection:
editor.tooltip: The entry and exit connection points used in conjunction with this (submachine) state, i.e. as targets and sources, respectively, in the region with the submachine state. A connection point reference references the corresponding definition of a connection point pseudostate in the statemachine referenced by the submachinestate.

editor.label: Connection Point:
editor.tooltip: The entry and exit pseudostates of a composite state. These can only be entry or exit Pseudostates, and they must have different names. They can only be defined for composite states.

editor.label: Redefined State:
editor.tooltip: The state of which this state is a redefinition.

editor.label: State Invariant:
editor.tooltip: Specifies conditions that are always true when this state is the current state. In protocol state machines, state invariants are additional conditions to the preconditions of the outgoing transitions, and to the postcondition of the incoming transitions.

editor.label: Entry:
editor.tooltip: An optional behavior that is executed whenever this state is entered regardless of the transition taken to reach the state. If defined, entry actions are always executed to completion prior to any internal behavior or transitions performed within the state.

editor.label: Exit:
editor.tooltip: An optional behavior that is executed whenever this state is exited regardless of which transition was taken out of the state. If defined, exit actions are always executed to completion only after all internal activities and transition actions have completed execution.

editor.label: Do Activity:
editor.tooltip: An optional behavior that is executed while being in the state. The execution starts when this state is entered, and stops either by itself, or when the state is exited, whichever comes first.

editor.label: Deferrable Trigger:
editor.tooltip: A list of triggers that are candidates to be retained by the state machine if they trigger no transitions out of the state (not consumed). A deferred trigger is retained until the state machine reaches a state configuration where it is no longer deferred.

editor.label: Region:
editor.tooltip: The regions owned directly by the state.

editor.label: Entry:
editor.tooltip: The entryPoint kind pseudo states corresponding to this connection point.

editor.label: Exit:
editor.tooltip: The exitPoints kind pseudo states corresponding to this connection point.

editor.label: State:
editor.tooltip: The State in which the connection point refreshens are defined.

editor.label: Kind:
editor.tooltip: Determines the precise type of the Pseudostate and can be one of: entryPoint, exitPoint, initial, deepHistory, shallowHistory, join, fork, junction, terminate or choice.

editor.label: State Machine:
editor.tooltip: The StateMachine in which this Pseudostate is defined. This only applies to Pseudostates of the kind entryPoint or exitPoint.

editor.label: State:
editor.tooltip: The State that owns this pseudostate and in which it appears.

editor.label: General Machine:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the protocol state machine to which the specific state machine conforms.

editor.label: Specific Machine:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the state machine which conforms to the general state machine.

editor.label: Owned Port:
editor.tooltip: References a set of ports that an encapsulated classifier owns.

editor.label: Owned Attribute:
editor.tooltip: References the properties owned by the classifier.

editor.label: Part:
editor.tooltip: References the properties specifying instances that the classifier owns by composition. This association is derived, selecting those owned properties where isComposite is true.

editor.label: Role:
editor.tooltip: References the roles that instances may play in this classifier.

editor.label: Owned Connector:
editor.tooltip: References the connectors owned by the classifier.

editor.label: Kind:
editor.tooltip: Indicates the kind of connector.

editor.label: Type:
editor.tooltip: An optional association that specifies the link corresponding to this connector.

editor.label: Redefined Connector:
editor.tooltip: A connector may be redefined when its containing classifier is specialized. The redefining connector may have a type that specializes the type of the redefined connector. The types of the connector ends of the redefining connector may specialize the types of the connector ends of the redefined connector. The properties of the connector ends of the redefining connector may be replaced.

editor.label: End:
editor.tooltip: A connector consists of at least two connector ends, each representing the participation of instances of the classifiers typing the connectable elements attached to this end. The set of connector ends is ordered.

editor.label: Contract:
editor.tooltip: The set of Behaviors that specify the valid interaction patterns across the connector.

editor.label: Metaclass:
editor.tooltip: References the Class that is extended through an Extension. The property is derived from the type of the memberEnd that is not the ownedEnd.

editor.label: Icon:
editor.tooltip: Stereotype can change the graphical appearance of the extended model element by using attached icons. When this association is not null, it references the location of the icon content to be displayed within diagrams presenting the extended model elements.

editor.label: Content:
editor.tooltip: This contains the serialization of the image according to the format. The value could represent a bitmap, image such as a GIF file, or drawing 'instructions' using a standard such as Scalable Vector Graphic (SVG) (which is XML based).

editor.label: Location:
editor.tooltip: This contains a location that can be used by a tool to locate the image as an alternative to embedding it in the stereotype.

editor.label: Format:
editor.tooltip: This indicates the format of the content - which is how the string content should be interpreted. The following values are reserved: SVG, GIF, PNG, JPG, WMF, EMF, BMP.In addition the prefix 'MIME: ' is also reserved. This option can be used as an alternative to express the reserved values above, for example "SVG" could instead be expressed as "MIME: image/svg+xml".

editor.label: Owned Stereotype:
editor.tooltip: References the Stereotypes that are owned by the Profile.

editor.label: Metaclass Reference:
editor.tooltip: References a metaclass that may be extended.

editor.label: Metamodel Reference:
editor.tooltip: References a package containing (directly or indirectly) metaclasses that may be extended.

editor.label: Viewpoint:
editor.tooltip: The name of the viewpoint that is expressed by a model (This name may refer to a profile definition).

editor.label: Parameter:
editor.tooltip: Parameters in the parameter set.

editor.label: Condition:
editor.tooltip: Constraint that should be satisfied for the owner of the parameters in an input parameter set to start execution using the values provided for those parameters, or the owner of the parameters in an output parameter set to end execution providing the values for those parameters, if all preconditions and conditions on input parameter sets were satisfied.

editor.label: Owned Attribute:
editor.tooltip: The Attributes owned by the DataType.

editor.label: Owned Operation:
editor.tooltip: The Operations owned by the DataType.

editor.label: Is Read Only:
editor.tooltip: States whether the feature's value may be modified by a client.

editor.label: Type:
editor.tooltip: The collaboration which is used in this occurrence. The collaboration defines the cooperation between its roles which are mapped to properties of the classifier owning the collaboration use.

editor.label: Role Binding:
editor.tooltip: A mapping between features of the collaboration type and features of the classifier or operation. This mapping indicates which connectable element of the classifier or operation plays which role(s) in the collaboration. A connectable element may be bound to multiple roles in the same collaboration use (that is, it may play multiple roles).

editor.label: Collaboration Role:
editor.tooltip: References connectable elements (possibly owned by other classifiers) which represent roles that instances may play in this collaboration.

editor.label: Include:
editor.tooltip: References the Include relationships owned by this use case.

editor.label: Extend:
editor.tooltip: References the Extend relationships owned by this use case.

editor.label: Extension Point:
editor.tooltip: References the ExtensionPoints owned by the use case.

editor.label: Subject:
editor.tooltip: References the subjects to which this use case applies. The subject or its parts realize all the use cases that apply to this subject. Use cases need not be attached to any specific subject, however. The subject may, but need not, own the use cases that apply to it.

editor.label: Addition:
editor.tooltip: References the use case that is to be included.

editor.label: Including Case:
editor.tooltip: References the use case which will include the addition and owns the include relationship.

editor.label: Extended Case:
editor.tooltip: References the use case that is being extended.

editor.label: Condition:
editor.tooltip: References the condition that must hold when the first extension point is reached for the extension to take place. If no constraint is associated with the extend relationship, the extension is unconditional.

editor.label: Extension Location:
editor.tooltip: An ordered list of extension points belonging to the extended use case, specifying where the respective behavioral fragments of the extending use case are to be inserted. The first fragment in the extending use case is associated with the first extension point in the list, the second fragment with the second point, and so on. (Note that, in most practical cases, the extending use case has just a single behavior fragment, so that the list of extension points is trivial.)

editor.label: Extension:
editor.tooltip: References the use case that represents the extension and owns the extend relationship.

editor.label: Use Case:
editor.tooltip: References the use case that owns this extension point.

editor.label: Extended Signature:
editor.tooltip: The template signature that is extended by this template signature.

editor.label: Inherited Parameter:
editor.tooltip: The formal template parameters of the extendedSignature.

editor.label: Classifier:
editor.tooltip: The classifier that owns this template signature.

editor.label: Allow Substitutable:
editor.tooltip: Constrains the required relationship between an actual parameter and the parameteredElement for this formal parameter.

editor.label: Constraining Classifier:
editor.tooltip: The classifiers that constrain the argument that can be used for the parameter. If the allowSubstitutable attribute is true, then any classifier that is compatible with this constraining classifier can be substituted; otherwise, it must be either this classifier or one of its subclasses. If this property is empty, there are no constraints on the classifier that can be used as an argument.

editor.label: Sub Expression:
editor.tooltip: The StringExpressions that constitute this StringExpression.

editor.label: Owning Expression:
editor.tooltip: The string expression of which this expression is a substring.

editor.label: Symbol:
editor.tooltip: The symbol associated with the node in the expression tree.

editor.label: Operand:
editor.tooltip: Specifies a sequence of operands.

editor.label: Merged Package:
editor.tooltip: References the Package that is to be merged with the receiving package of the PackageMerge.

editor.label: Receiving Package:
editor.tooltip: References the Package that is being extended with the contents of the merged package of the PackageMerge.

editor.label: Is Strict:
editor.tooltip: Specifies that the Profile filtering rules for the metaclasses of the referenced metamodel shall be strictly applied.

editor.label: Applied Profile:
editor.tooltip: References the Profiles that are applied to a Package through this ProfileApplication.

editor.label: Applying Package:
editor.tooltip: The package that owns the profile application.

editor.label: Owned Literal:
editor.tooltip: The ordered set of literals for this Enumeration.

editor.label: Enumeration:
editor.tooltip: The Enumeration that this EnumerationLiteral is a member of.

editor.label: Classifier:
editor.tooltip: The classifier or classifiers of the represented instance. If multiple classifiers are specified, the instance is classified by all of them.

editor.label: Slot:
editor.tooltip: A slot giving the value or values of a structural feature of the instance. An instance specification can have one slot per structural feature of its classifiers, including inherited features. It is not necessary to model a slot for each structural feature, in which case the instance specification is a partial description.

editor.label: Specification:
editor.tooltip: A specification of how to compute, derive, or construct the instance.

editor.label: Defining Feature:
editor.tooltip: The structural feature that specifies the values that may be held by the slot.

editor.label: Value:
editor.tooltip: The value or values corresponding to the defining feature for the owning instance specification.

editor.label: Owning Instance:
editor.tooltip: The instance specification that owns this slot.

editor.label: Value:
editor.tooltip: The specified Integer value.

editor.label: Value:
editor.tooltip: The specified String value.

editor.label: Value:
editor.tooltip: The specified Boolean value.

editor.label: Instance:
editor.tooltip: The instance that is the specified value.

editor.label: Value:
editor.tooltip: The specified UnlimitedNatural value.

editor.label: Body:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the behavior in one or more languages.

editor.label: Language:
editor.tooltip: Languages the body strings use in the same order as the body strings.

editor.label: Body:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the action in one or more languages.

editor.label: Language:
editor.tooltip: Languages the body strings use, in the same order as the body strings

editor.label: Input Value:
editor.tooltip: Provides input to the action.

editor.label: Output Value:
editor.tooltip: Takes output from the action.

editor.label: Output:
editor.tooltip: The ordered set of output pins connected to the Action. The action places its results onto pins in this set.

editor.label: Input:
editor.tooltip: The ordered set of input pins connected to the Action. These are among the total set of inputs.

editor.label: Context:
editor.tooltip: The classifier that owns the behavior of which this action is a part.

editor.label: Local Precondition:
editor.tooltip: Constraint that must be satisfied when execution is started.

editor.label: Local Postcondition:
editor.tooltip: Constraint that must be satisfied when executed is completed.

editor.label: Handler:
editor.tooltip: A set of exception handlers that are examined if an uncaught exception propagates to the outer level of the executable node.

editor.label: In Structured Node:
editor.tooltip: Structured activity node containing the node.

editor.label: Activity:
editor.tooltip: Activity containing the node.

editor.label: Outgoing:
editor.tooltip: Edges that have the node as source.

editor.label: Incoming:
editor.tooltip: Edges that have the node as target.

editor.label: In Partition:
editor.tooltip: Partitions containing the node.

editor.label: In Interruptible Region:
editor.tooltip: Interruptible regions containing the node.

editor.label: In Group:
editor.tooltip: Groups containing the node.

editor.label: Redefined Node:
editor.tooltip: Inherited nodes replaced by this node in a specialization of the activity.

editor.label: Must Isolate:
editor.tooltip: If true, then the actions in the node execute in isolation from actions outside the node.

editor.label: Variable:
editor.tooltip: A variable defined in the scope of the structured activity node. It has no value and may not be accessed

editor.label: Edge:
editor.tooltip: Edges immediately contained in the structured node.

editor.label: Node:
editor.tooltip: Nodes immediately contained in the group.

editor.label: Subgroup:
editor.tooltip: Groups immediately contained in the group.

editor.label: Super Group:
editor.tooltip: Group immediately containing the group.

editor.label: In Activity:
editor.tooltip: Activity containing the group.

editor.label: Contained Edge:
editor.tooltip: Edges immediately contained in the group.

editor.label: Contained Node:
editor.tooltip: Nodes immediately contained in the group.

editor.label: Is Read Only:
editor.tooltip: If true, this activity must not make any changes to variables outside the activity or to objects. (This is an assertion, not an executable property. It may be used by an execution engine to optimize model execution. If the assertion is violated by the action, then the model is ill-formed.) The default is false (an activity may make nonlocal changes).

editor.label: Is Single Execution:
editor.tooltip: If true, all invocations of the activity are handled by the same execution.

editor.label: Structured Node:
editor.tooltip: Top-level structured nodes in the activity.

editor.label: Variable:
editor.tooltip: Top-level variables in the activity.

editor.label: Node:
editor.tooltip: Nodes coordinated by the activity.

editor.label: Edge:
editor.tooltip: Edges expressing flow between nodes of the activity.

editor.label: Partition:
editor.tooltip: Top-level partitions in the activity.

editor.label: Group:
editor.tooltip: Top-level groups in the activity.

editor.label: Scope:
editor.tooltip: A structured activity node that owns the variable.

editor.label: Activity Scope:
editor.tooltip: An activity that owns the variable.

editor.label: Source:
editor.tooltip: Node from which tokens are taken when they traverse the edge.

editor.label: Target:
editor.tooltip: Node to which tokens are put when they traverse the edge.

editor.label: Redefined Edge:
editor.tooltip: Inherited edges replaced by this edge in a specialization of the activity.

editor.label: In Partition:
editor.tooltip: Partitions containing the edge.

editor.label: Guard:
editor.tooltip: Specification evaluated at runtime to determine if the edge can be traversed.

editor.label: Weight:
editor.tooltip: The minimum number of tokens that must traverse the edge at the same time.

editor.label: Interrupts:
editor.tooltip: Region that the edge can interrupt.

editor.label: In Structured Node:
editor.tooltip: Structured activity node containing the edge.

editor.label: In Group:
editor.tooltip: Groups containing the edge.

editor.label: Activity:
editor.tooltip: Activity containing the edge.

editor.label: Is Dimension:
editor.tooltip: Tells whether the partition groups other partitions along a dimension.

editor.label: Is External:
editor.tooltip: Tells whether the partition represents an entity to which the partitioning structure does not apply.

editor.label: Node:
editor.tooltip: Nodes immediately contained in the group.

editor.label: Subpartition:
editor.tooltip: Partitions immediately contained in the partition.

editor.label: Super Partition:
editor.tooltip: Partition immediately containing the partition.

editor.label: Represents:
editor.tooltip: An element constraining behaviors invoked by nodes in the partition.

editor.label: Edge:
editor.tooltip: Edges immediately contained in the group.

editor.label: Node:
editor.tooltip: Nodes immediately contained in the group.

editor.label: Interrupting Edge:
editor.tooltip: The edges leaving the region that will abort other tokens flowing in the region.

editor.label: Handler Body:
editor.tooltip: A node that is executed if the handler satisfies an uncaught exception.

editor.label: Exception Input:
editor.tooltip: An object node within the handler body. When the handler catches an exception, the exception token is placed in this node, causing the body to execute.

editor.label: Exception Type:
editor.tooltip: The kind of instances that the handler catches. If an exception occurs whose type is any of the classifiers in the set, the handler catches the exception and executes its body.

editor.label: Protected Node:
editor.tooltip: The node protected by the handler. The handler is examined if an exception propagates to the outside of the node.

editor.label: Ordering:
editor.tooltip: Tells whether and how the tokens in the object node are ordered for selection to traverse edges outgoing from the object node.

editor.label: Is Control Type:
editor.tooltip: Tells whether the type of the object node is to be treated as control.

editor.label: Upper Bound:
editor.tooltip: The maximum number of tokens allowed in the node. Objects cannot flow into the node if the upper bound is reached.

editor.label: In State:
editor.tooltip: The required states of the object available at this point in the activity.

editor.label: Selection:
editor.tooltip: Selects tokens for outgoing edges.

editor.label: Is Control:
editor.tooltip: Tells whether the pins provide data to the actions, or just controls when it executes it.

editor.label: Is Synchronous:
editor.tooltip: If true, the call is synchronous and the caller waits for completion of the invoked behavior.If false, the call is asynchronous and the caller proceeds immediately and does not expect a return values.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: A list of output pins where the results of performing the invocation are placed.

editor.label: Argument:
editor.tooltip: Specification of the ordered set of argument values that appears during execution.

editor.label: On Port:
editor.tooltip: A optional port of the receiver object on which the behavioral feature is invoked.

editor.label: Target:
editor.tooltip: The target object to which the signal is sent.

editor.label: Signal:
editor.tooltip: The type of signal transmitted to the target object.

editor.label: Operation:
editor.tooltip: The operation to be invoked by the action execution.

editor.label: Target:
editor.tooltip: The target object to which the request is sent. The classifier of the target object is used to dynamically determine a behavior to invoke. This object constitutes the context of the execution of the operation.

editor.label: Behavior:
editor.tooltip: The invoked behavior. It must be capable of accepting and returning control.

editor.label: Executable Node:
editor.tooltip: An ordered set of executable nodes.

editor.label: Parameter:
editor.tooltip: The parameter the object node will be accepting or providing values for.

editor.label: Value:
editor.tooltip: Value that the pin will provide.

editor.label: Message Sort:
editor.tooltip: The sort of communication reflected by the Message

editor.label: Receive Event:
editor.tooltip: References the Receiving of the Message

editor.label: Send Event:
editor.tooltip: References the Sending of the Message.

editor.label: Connector:
editor.tooltip: The Connector on which this Message is sent.

editor.label: Interaction:
editor.tooltip: The enclosing Interaction owning the Message

editor.label: Argument:
editor.tooltip: The arguments of the Message

editor.label: Signature:
editor.tooltip: The definition of the type or signature of the Message (depending on its kind). The associated named element is derived from the message end that constitutes the sending or receiving message event. If both a sending event and a receiving message event are present, the signature is obtained from the sending event.

editor.label: Message:
editor.tooltip: References a Message.

editor.label: Lifeline:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the participants in this Interaction.

editor.label: Fragment:
editor.tooltip: The ordered set of fragments in the Interaction.

editor.label: Action:
editor.tooltip: Actions owned by the Interaction.

editor.label: Formal Gate:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the gates that form the message interface between this Interaction and any InteractionUses which reference it.

editor.label: Message:
editor.tooltip: The Messages contained in this Interaction.

editor.label: Covered:
editor.tooltip: References the Lifelines that the InteractionFragment involves.

editor.label: General Ordering:
editor.tooltip: The general ordering relationships contained in this fragment.

editor.label: Enclosing Interaction:
editor.tooltip: The Interaction enclosing this InteractionFragment.

editor.label: Enclosing Operand:
editor.tooltip: The operand enclosing this InteractionFragment (they may nest recursively)

editor.label: Represents:
editor.tooltip: References the ConnectableElement within the classifier that contains the enclosing interaction.

editor.label: Interaction:
editor.tooltip: References the Interaction enclosing this Lifeline.

editor.label: Selector:
editor.tooltip: If the referenced ConnectableElement is multivalued, then this specifies the specific individual part within that set.

editor.label: Decomposed As:
editor.tooltip: References the Interaction that represents the decomposition.

editor.label: Covered By:
editor.tooltip: References the InteractionFragments in which this Lifeline takes part.

editor.label: Refers To:
editor.tooltip: Refers to the Interaction that defines its meaning

editor.label: Actual Gate:
editor.tooltip: The actual gates of the InteractionUse

editor.label: Argument:
editor.tooltip: The actual arguments of the Interaction

editor.label: Before:
editor.tooltip: The OccurrenceSpecification referenced comes before the OccurrenceSpecification referenced by after.

editor.label: After:
editor.tooltip: The OccurrenceSpecification referenced comes after the OccurrenceSpecification referenced by before.

editor.label: To Before:
editor.tooltip: References the GeneralOrderings that specify EventOcurrences that must occur before this OccurrenceSpecification

editor.label: Event:
editor.tooltip: References a specification of the occurring event.

editor.label: To After:
editor.tooltip: References the GeneralOrderings that specify EventOcurrences that must occur after this OccurrenceSpecification

editor.label: Guard:
editor.tooltip: Constraint of the operand.

editor.label: Fragment:
editor.tooltip: The fragments of the operand.

editor.label: Minint:
editor.tooltip: The minimum number of iterations of a loop

editor.label: Maxint:
editor.tooltip: The maximum number of iterations of a loop

editor.label: Start:
editor.tooltip: References the OccurrenceSpecification that designates the start of the Action or Behavior

editor.label: Finish:
editor.tooltip: References the OccurrenceSpecification that designates the finish of the Action or Behavior.

editor.label: Invariant:
editor.tooltip: A Constraint that should hold at runtime for this StateInvariant

editor.label: Action:
editor.tooltip: Action whose execution is occurring.

editor.label: Behavior:
editor.tooltip: Behavior whose execution is occurring.

editor.label: Operation:
editor.tooltip: The operation associated with this event.

editor.label: Signal:
editor.tooltip: The signal associated with this event.

editor.label: Execution:
editor.tooltip: References the execution specification describing the execution that is started or finished at this execution event.

editor.label: Operation:
editor.tooltip: The operation associated with this event.

editor.label: Signal:
editor.tooltip: The signal associated with this event.

editor.label: Operation:
editor.tooltip: Designates the operation whose invocation raised the call event.

editor.label: Change Expression:
editor.tooltip: A Boolean-valued expression that will result in a change event whenever its value changes from false to true.

editor.label: Signal:
editor.tooltip: The specific signal that is associated with this event.

editor.label: Decision Input:
editor.tooltip: Provides input to guard specifications on edges outgoing from the decision node.

editor.label: Decision Input Flow:
editor.tooltip: An additional edge incoming to the decision node that provides a decision input value.

editor.label: Is Multicast:
editor.tooltip: Tells whether the objects in the flow are passed by multicasting.

editor.label: Is Multireceive:
editor.tooltip: Tells whether the objects in the flow are gathered from respondents to multicasting.

editor.label: Transformation:
editor.tooltip: Changes or replaces data tokens flowing along edge.

editor.label: Selection:
editor.tooltip: Selects tokens from a source object node.

editor.label: Abstraction:
editor.tooltip: The Component that owns this ComponentRealization and which is implemented by its realizing classifiers.

editor.label: Realizing Classifier:
editor.tooltip: The classifiers that are involved in the implementation of the Component that owns this Realization.

editor.label: Is Indirectly Instantiated:
editor.tooltip: The kind of instantiation that applies to a Component. If false, the component is instantiated as an addressable object. If true, the Component is defined at design-time, but at runtime (or execution-time) an object specified by the Component does not exist, that is, the component is instantiated indirectly, through the instantiation of its realizing classifiers or parts. Several standard stereotypes use this meta attribute, e.g. <<specification>>, <<focus>>, <<subsystem>>.

editor.label: Required:
editor.tooltip: The interfaces that the component requires from other components in its environment in order to be able to offer its full set of provided functionality. These interfaces may be used by the Component or any of its realizingClassifiers, or they may be the Interfaces that are required by its public Ports.

editor.label: Provided:
editor.tooltip: The interfaces that the component exposes to its environment. These interfaces may be Realized by the Component or any of its realizingClassifiers, or they may be the Interfaces that are provided by its public Ports.

editor.label: Packaged Element:
editor.tooltip: The set of PackageableElements that a Component owns. In the namespace of a component, all model elements that are involved in or related to its definition may be owned or imported explicitly. These may include e.g. Classes, Interfaces, Components, Packages, Use cases, Dependencies (e.g. mappings), and Artifacts.

editor.label: Realization:
editor.tooltip: The set of Realizations owned by the Component. Realizations reference the Classifiers of which the Component is an abstraction; i.e., that realize its behavior.

editor.label: Nested Node:
editor.tooltip: The Nodes that are defined (nested) within the Node.

editor.label: Interaction Operator:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the operation which defines the semantics of this combination of InteractionFragments.

editor.label: Operand:
editor.tooltip: The set of operands of the combined fragment.

editor.label: Cfragment Gate:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the gates that form the interface between this CombinedFragment and its surroundings

editor.label: Setting:
editor.tooltip: True: when the Continuation is at the end of the enclosing InteractionFragment and False when it is in the beginning.

editor.label: Message:
editor.tooltip: The set of messages that apply to this fragment

editor.label: Classifier:
editor.tooltip: Classifier to be instantiated.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: Gives the output pin on which the result is put.

editor.label: Is Destroy Links:
editor.tooltip: Specifies whether links in which the object participates are destroyed along with the object.

editor.label: Is Destroy Owned Objects:
editor.tooltip: Specifies whether objects owned by the object are destroyed along with the object.

editor.label: Target:
editor.tooltip: The input pin providing the object to be destroyed.

editor.label: First:
editor.tooltip: Gives the pin on which an object is placed.

editor.label: Second:
editor.tooltip: Gives the pin on which an object is placed.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: Tells whether the two input objects are identical.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: Gives the output pin on which the hosting object is placed.

editor.label: Structural Feature:
editor.tooltip: Structural feature to be read.

editor.label: Object:
editor.tooltip: Gives the input pin from which the object whose structural feature is to be read or written is obtained.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: Gives the output pin on which the result is put.

editor.label: Value:
editor.tooltip: Value to be added or removed from the structural feature.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: Gives the output pin on which the result is put.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: Gives the output pin on which the result is put.

editor.label: Is Remove Duplicates:
editor.tooltip: Specifies whether to remove duplicates of the value in nonunique structural features.

editor.label: Remove At:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the position of an existing value to remove in ordered nonunique structural features. The type of the pin is UnlimitedNatural, but the value cannot be zero or unlimited.

editor.label: Is Replace All:
editor.tooltip: Specifies whether existing values of the structural feature of the object should be removed before adding the new value.

editor.label: Insert At:
editor.tooltip: Gives the position at which to insert a new value or move an existing value in ordered structural features. The type of the pin is UnlimitedNatural, but the value cannot be zero. This pin is omitted for unordered structural features.

editor.label: End Data:
editor.tooltip: Data identifying one end of a link by the objects on its ends and qualifiers.

editor.label: Input Value:
editor.tooltip: Pins taking end objects and qualifier values as input.

editor.label: Value:
editor.tooltip: Input pin that provides the specified object for the given end. This pin is omitted if the link-end data specifies an 'open' end for reading.

editor.label: End:
editor.tooltip: Association end for which this link-end data specifies values.

editor.label: Qualifier:
editor.tooltip: List of qualifier values

editor.label: Qualifier:
editor.tooltip: Attribute representing the qualifier for which the value is to be specified.

editor.label: Value:
editor.tooltip: Input pin from which the specified value for the qualifier is taken.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: The pin on which are put the objects participating in the association at the end not specified by the inputs.

editor.label: Is Replace All:
editor.tooltip: Specifies whether the existing links emanating from the object on this end should be destroyed before creating a new link.

editor.label: Insert At:
editor.tooltip: Specifies where the new link should be inserted for ordered association ends, or where an existing link should be moved to. The type of the input is UnlimitedNatural, but the input cannot be zero. This pin is omitted for association ends that are not ordered.

editor.label: Is Destroy Duplicates:
editor.tooltip: Specifies whether to destroy duplicates of the value in nonunique association ends.

editor.label: Destroy At:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the position of an existing link to be destroyed in ordered nonunique association ends. The type of the pin is UnlimitedNatural, but the value cannot be zero or unlimited.

editor.label: Object:
editor.tooltip: Gives the input pin from which is obtained the object whose participation in the association is to be cleared.

editor.label: Association:
editor.tooltip: Association to be cleared.

editor.label: Signal:
editor.tooltip: The specification of signal object transmitted to the target objects.

editor.label: Target:
editor.tooltip: The target object to which the object is sent.

editor.label: Request:
editor.tooltip: The request object, which is transmitted to the target object. The object may be copied in transmission, so identity might not be preserved.

editor.label: Value:
editor.tooltip: Value specification to be evaluated.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: Gives the output pin on which the result is put.

editor.label: Expr:
editor.tooltip: The value of the time expression.

editor.label: Observation:
editor.tooltip: Refers to the time and duration observations that are involved in expr.

editor.label: Expr:
editor.tooltip: The value of the Duration.

editor.label: Observation:
editor.tooltip: Refers to the time and duration observations that are involved in expr.

editor.label: Min:
editor.tooltip: Refers to the ValueSpecification denoting the minimum value of the range.

editor.label: Max:
editor.tooltip: Refers to the ValueSpecification denoting the maximum value of the range.

editor.label: First Event:
editor.tooltip: The value of firstEvent is related to constrainedElement. If firstEvent is true, then the corresponding observation event is the first time instant the execution enters constrainedElement. If firstEvent is false, then the corresponding observation event is the last time instant the execution is within constrainedElement.

editor.label: First Event:
editor.tooltip: The value of firstEvent[i] is related to constrainedElement[i] (where i is 1 or 2). If firstEvent[i] is true, then the corresponding observation event is the first time instant the execution enters constrainedElement[i]. If firstEvent[i] is false, then the corresponding observation event is the last time instant the execution is within constrainedElement[i]. Default value is true applied when constrainedElement[i] refers an element that represents only one time instant.

editor.label: First Event:
editor.tooltip: The value of firstEvent is related to event. If firstEvent is true, then the corresponding observation event is the first time instant the execution enters event. If firstEvent is false, then the corresponding observation event is the time instant the execution exits event.

editor.label: Event:
editor.tooltip: The observation is determined by the entering or exiting of the event element during execution.

editor.label: First Event:
editor.tooltip: The value of firstEvent[i] is related to event[i] (where i is 1 or 2). If firstEvent[i] is true, then the corresponding observation event is the first time instant the execution enters event[i]. If firstEvent[i] is false, then the corresponding observation event is the time instant the execution exits event[i]. Default value is true applied when event[i] refers an element that represents only one time instant.

editor.label: Event:
editor.tooltip: The observation is determined by the entering or exiting of the event element during execution.

editor.label: Is Relative:
editor.tooltip: Specifies whether it is relative or absolute time.

editor.label: When:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the corresponding time deadline.

editor.label: Variable:
editor.tooltip: Variable to be read.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: Gives the output pin on which the result is put.

editor.label: Value:
editor.tooltip: Value to be added or removed from the variable.

editor.label: Is Replace All:
editor.tooltip: Specifies whether existing values of the variable should be removed before adding the new value.

editor.label: Insert At:
editor.tooltip: Gives the position at which to insert a new value or move an existing value in ordered variables. The types is UnlimitedINatural, but the value cannot be zero. This pin is omitted for unordered variables.

editor.label: Is Remove Duplicates:
editor.tooltip: Specifies whether to remove duplicates of the value in nonunique variables.

editor.label: Remove At:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the position of an existing value to remove in ordered nonunique variables. The type of the pin is UnlimitedNatural, but the value cannot be zero or unlimited.

editor.label: Exception:
editor.tooltip: An input pin whose value becomes an exception object.

editor.label: From Action:
editor.tooltip: The action used to provide values.

editor.label: Represented:
editor.tooltip: Determines the classifiers that will specify the structure and nature of the information. An information item represents all its represented classifiers.

editor.label: Realization:
editor.tooltip: Determines which Relationship will realize the specified flow

editor.label: Conveyed:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the information items that may circulate on this information flow.

editor.label: Information Source:
editor.tooltip: Defines from which source the conveyed InformationItems are initiated.

editor.label: Information Target:
editor.tooltip: Defines to which target the conveyed InformationItems are directed.

editor.label: Realizing Activity Edge:
editor.tooltip: Determines which ActivityEdges will realize the specified flow.

editor.label: Realizing Connector:
editor.tooltip: Determines which Connectors will realize the specified flow.

editor.label: Realizing Message:
editor.tooltip: Determines which Messages will realize the specified flow.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: The runtime instances of the classifier.

editor.label: Classifier:
editor.tooltip: The classifier whose instances are to be retrieved.

editor.label: Is Replace All:
editor.tooltip: Specifies whether existing classifiers should be removed before adding the new classifiers.

editor.label: Old Classifier:
editor.tooltip: A set of classifiers to be removed from the classifiers of the object.

editor.label: New Classifier:
editor.tooltip: A set of classifiers to be added to the classifiers of the object.

editor.label: Object:
editor.tooltip: Holds the object to be reclassified.

editor.label: Is Direct:
editor.tooltip: Indicates whether the classifier must directly classify the input object.

editor.label: Classifier:
editor.tooltip: The classifier against which the classification of the input object is tested.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: After termination of the action, will hold the result of the test.

editor.label: Object:
editor.tooltip: Holds the object whose classification is to be tested.

editor.label: Object:
editor.tooltip: Holds the object on which to start the owned behavior.

editor.label: Object:
editor.tooltip: Gives the input pin from which the link object is obtained.

editor.label: End:
editor.tooltip: Link end to be read.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: Pin where the result value is placed.

editor.label: Object:
editor.tooltip: Gives the input pin from which the link object is obtained.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: Pin where the result value is placed.

editor.label: Qualifier:
editor.tooltip: The attribute representing the qualifier to be read.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: Gives the output pin on which the result is put.

editor.label: Is Unmarshall:
editor.tooltip: Indicates whether there is a single output pin for the event, or multiple output pins for attributes of the event.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: Pins holding the received event objects or their attributes. Event objects may be copied in transmission, so identity might not be preserved.

editor.label: Trigger:
editor.tooltip: The type of events accepted by the action, as specified by triggers. For triggers with signal events, a signal of the specified type or any subtype of the specified signal type is accepted.

editor.label: Return Information:
editor.tooltip: Pin where a value is placed containing sufficient information to perform a subsequent reply and return control to the caller. The contents of this value are opaque. It can be passed and copied but it cannot be manipulated by the model.

editor.label: Reply To Call:
editor.tooltip: The trigger specifying the operation whose call is being replied to.

editor.label: Return Information:
editor.tooltip: A pin containing the return information value produced by an earlier AcceptCallAction.

editor.label: Reply Value:
editor.tooltip: A list of pins containing the reply values of the operation. These values are returned to the caller.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: The values of the structural features of the input object.

editor.label: Unmarshall Type:
editor.tooltip: The type of the object to be unmarshalled.

editor.label: Object:
editor.tooltip: The object to be unmarshalled.

editor.label: Is Ordered:
editor.tooltip: Tells whether the order of the input collection should determine the order in which the behavior is applied to its elements.

editor.label: Reducer:
editor.tooltip: Behavior that is applied to two elements of the input collection to produce a value that is the same type as elements of the collection.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: Gives the output pin on which the result is put.

editor.label: Collection:
editor.tooltip: The collection to be reduced.

editor.label: Object:
editor.tooltip: Holds the object which is either a behavior to be started or has a classifier behavior to be started.

editor.label: Is Combine Duplicate:
editor.tooltip: Tells whether tokens having objects with the same identity are combined into one by the join.

editor.label: Join Spec:
editor.tooltip: A specification giving the conditions under which the join with emit a token. Default is "and".

editor.label: Is Determinate:
editor.tooltip: If true, the modeler asserts that at most one test will succeed.

editor.label: Is Assured:
editor.tooltip: If true, the modeler asserts that at least one test will succeed.

editor.label: Clause:
editor.tooltip: Set of clauses composing the conditional.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: A list of output pins that constitute the data flow outputs of the conditional.

editor.label: Test:
editor.tooltip: A nested activity fragment with a designated output pin that specifies the result of the test.

editor.label: Body:
editor.tooltip: A nested activity fragment that is executed if the test evaluates to true and the clause is chosen over any concurrent clauses that also evaluate to true.

editor.label: Predecessor Clause:
editor.tooltip: A set of clauses whose tests must all evaluate false before the current clause can be tested.

editor.label: Successor Clause:
editor.tooltip: A set of clauses which may not be tested unless the current clause tests false.

editor.label: Decider:
editor.tooltip: An output pin within the test fragment the value of which is examined after execution of the test to determine whether the body should be executed.

editor.label: Body Output:
editor.tooltip: A list of output pins within the body fragment whose values are moved to the result pins of the containing conditional node after execution of the clause body.

editor.label: Is Tested First:
editor.tooltip: If true, the test is performed before the first execution of the body.If false, the body is executed once before the test is performed.

editor.label: Body Part:
editor.tooltip: The set of nodes and edges that perform the repetitive computations of the loop. The body section is executed as long as the test section produces a true value.

editor.label: Setup Part:
editor.tooltip: The set of nodes and edges that initialize values or perform other setup computations for the loop.

editor.label: Decider:
editor.tooltip: An output pin within the test fragment the value of which is examined after execution of the test to determine whether to execute the loop body.

editor.label: Test:
editor.tooltip: The set of nodes, edges, and designated value that compute a Boolean value to determine if another execution of the body will be performed.

editor.label: Result:
editor.tooltip: A list of output pins that constitute the data flow output of the entire loop.

editor.label: Loop Variable:
editor.tooltip: A list of output pins that hold the values of the loop variables during an execution of the loop. When the test fails, the values are movied to the result pins of the loop.

editor.label: Body Output:
editor.tooltip: A list of output pins within the body fragment the values of which are moved to the loop variable pins after completion of execution of the body, before the next iteration of the loop begins or before the loop exits.

editor.label: Loop Variable Input:
editor.tooltip: A list of values that are moved into the loop variable pins before the first iteration of the loop.

editor.label: Region As Output:
editor.tooltip: The expansion region for which the node is an output.

editor.label: Region As Input:
editor.tooltip: The expansion region for which the node is an input.

editor.label: Mode:
editor.tooltip: The way in which the executions interact:parallel: all interactions are independentiterative: the interactions occur in order of the elementsstream: a stream of values flows into a single execution

editor.label: Input Element:
editor.tooltip: An object node that holds a separate element of the input collection during each of the multiple executions of the region.

editor.label: Output Element:
editor.tooltip: An object node that accepts a separate element of the output collection during each of the multiple executions of the region. The values are formed into a collection that is available when the execution of the region is complete.

editor.label: Post Condition:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the post condition of the transition which is the condition that should be obtained once the transition is triggered. This post condition is part of the post condition of the operation connected to the transition.

editor.label: Referred:
editor.tooltip: This association refers to the associated operation. It is derived from the operation of the call trigger when applicable.

editor.label: Pre Condition:
editor.tooltip: Specifies the precondition of the transition. It specifies the condition that should be verified before triggering the transition. This guard condition added to the source state will be evaluated as part of the precondition of the operation referred by the transition if any.
